<TITLE> Hasina suffering from fever: spokesman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 21 (bdnews24.com)  Former prime minister Sheikh Hasina, now in the US for medical treatment, is running temperature, a spokesman said Saturday. "She had fever last night. She was very sick all day yesterday," the spokesman told bdnews24.com around 11am Washington time Saturday. "She still has fever and been complaining of ear problems." "The temperature shot up to 103," the spokesman said. Hasina flew to Washington from Boston on Thursday and is set to fly to Orlando for ear treatment, said the spokesman, reached by phone around 9pm Bangladesh time. The Awami League chief reached Boston of Massachusetts on June 13, a day after she was freed from jail in Dhaka to seek medical treatment abroad. bdn
